[h2 id=Versions 
	" Versions
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Mixed-Up Mother Goose
	]em
	" is a Sierra adventure game.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The game was
	$LF
	[a href=https://wiki.scummvm.org/index.php/Mixed-Up_Mother_Goose#Versions rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"remade and rereleased several times
	]a
	".
	$LF
	"This article is about the original 1987
	$LF
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adventure_Game_Interpreter rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"AGI
	]a
	" version for DOS.
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=Tools 
	" Tools
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"Utilities for reverse engineering, routing, etc. from 
	(__wikiLink|href=/5088M|implicitdisplaytext=5088M)
	":
	$LF
]div
[pre 
	"git clone https://www.bamsoftware.com/git/mumg.git
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	[a href=http://agiwiki.sierrahelp.com/index.php?title=Agikit rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"agikit
	]a
	$LF
	"is useful for decompiling game logic.
	$LF
	"The 
	[a href=http://agiwiki.sierrahelp.com/index.php?title=Main_Page rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"AGI Programmer's Wiki
	]a
	$LF
	"is useful in general.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"See 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Forum/Topics/23454|implicitdisplaytext=Forum/Topics/23454)
	" for notes on the development of 
	(__wikiLink|href=/5088M|implicitdisplaytext=5088M)
	".
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=Map 
	" Map
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	[a href=https://www.bamsoftware.com/computers/tasvideos/mumg-map-revised.svg rel=noopener external nofollow 
		[img alt=Game map, a 7×5 grid of overworld rooms with 9 additional interior rooms class=embed mw-100 src=https://www.bamsoftware.com/computers/tasvideos/mumg-map-revised.png 
		]img
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There are 44 
	[a href=http://agiwiki.sierrahelp.com/index.php?title=Room rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"rooms
	]a
	",
	$LF
	"which are internally numbered 1–44.
	$LF
	"Rooms 1–35 are overworld rooms.
	$LF
	"Rooms 36–44 are interior rooms.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Blue circles in the diagram show the destination rooms
	$LF
	"to which the numbered items 18–30 have to be delivered.
	$LF
	"Gold squares show where random item assignment may place items;
	$LF
	"see below.
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=Items 
	" Items
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"There are 20 items, numbered 11–30.
	$LF
	"Items 11–17 are "walking" items that follow the player
	$LF
	"around while they are in the inventory.
	$LF
	"Items 18–30 are "pocket" items that disappear from the screen
	$LF
	"while they are in the inventory.
	$LF
	"The important difference is that walking items
	$LF
	"cannot remain in interior rooms:
	$LF
	"the initial random items assignment will not
	$LF
	"place a walking item in an interior room,
	$LF
	"and if you swap a walking item for another item
	$LF
	"while in an interior room,
	$LF
	"the walking item will not remain there,
	$LF
	"but will warp to some other overworld room.
	$LF
]div
